The '''Cracken Flight Group''', also known as '''Cracken's Flight Group''', was the name given to the [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] in [[Pash Cracken]]'s [[Fighter wing/Legends|wing]] of [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE Fighters]] whom he led in a defection from the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] to the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]]. Their destruction of the ''[[Exsanguinator]]'' made the flight and their leader legendary.

The pilots of the Cracken Flight Group earned a reputation in the [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Alliance Fleet]] for hit-and-fade raids, including one of the first raids by an [[RZ-1 A-wing interceptor/Legends|A-wing]] [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]].

When his unit was forced to abandon their base at [[Xyquine II]], Cracken developed the [[Cracken Twist]] to fool the Imperial assault force. Cracken had high personal success in his interceptor, but his reckless methods proved too inspiring to his pilots, and a few perished trying to replicate their leader's luck. Frustrated, Cracken requested and received a transfer to [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]]' [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]], where he flew as [[Rogue Four/Legends|Rogue Four]].

Cracken returned to his flight group after his stint with the Rogues, and led them during [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn's]] campaign against the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[9 ABY/Legends|five years after]] the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]].

